description:
&lt;p&gt;Lancashire and South Cumbria Foundation Trust (LSCFT) are currently investing in the mental health services provided in south Cumbria. LSCFT currently provides a 15 bedded mixed sex dementia inpatient unit in Barrow in Furness which provides assessment intervention and treatment to patients with Dementia. Throughout the patient’s admission an individual care package will be identified to support their future needs and that of their Families and Carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barrow in Furness is located in an enviable location it is surrounded by the sea and with easy accessible routes into the Lake District. It has internationally renowned wildlife sites and a wealth of industrial and historical heritage sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated Staff nurses who are passionate about older people’s care and will be committed to the ongoing service development. The successful candidates must be able to demonstrate excellent clinical and interpersonal qualities, have a positive outlook and ensure that delivering a quality service, which genuinely engages with service users, carers and other stakeholders, is a key priority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will be required to work shifts covering 24 hours, seven days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications from RMN’s who are &lt;strong&gt;currently registered with the NMC or from student nurses due to register before April 2021.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You may also be eligible for a Relocation Package or Golden Hello incentives (subject to confirmation). Apply now for further details&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt; This post is subject to an enhanced DBS Clearance. As part of the pre-employment checks, successful candidates will be required to pay for their own DBS check at a cost of £46. Deductions will be taken from the first 3 months salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are not invited to interview within 3 weeks of the closing date, then please assume that on this occasion you have been unsuccessful, as it is not possible to contact all unsuccessful candidates. It is important that applicants log in to the website and check their Trac account on a regular basis to read and respond to any emails they may have received. If you do not have regular access to email/internet please advise the team of suitable contact details.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All posts are subject to the nationally agreed Agenda for Change terms and conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jo Waterston &lt;/strong&gt;on &lt;strong&gt;01229 &lt;strong&gt;404543&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
